Student Record Management System (C Program)
рҹ”№ 1. Title
Student Record Management System using File Handling in C
рҹ”№ 2. Objective
To develop a C program that:
Accepts student details (name, roll number, marks)
Calculates average and grade
Stores the data permanently in a file
рҹ”№ 3. Description
This program allows the user to enter student details and calculates their academic performance. The calculated result is displayed on the screen and stored in a file named student_records.txt using file handling in append mode.
рҹ”№ 4. Features
Takes input for student details
Calculates average marks
Assigns grade based on average
Saves records in a file
Supports multiple entries (append mode)
рҹ”№ 5. Algorithm
Start
Declare variables (name, roll number, marks, average, grade)
Open file student_records.txt in append mode
If file opening fails
вҶ’ Display error and stop
Input student name
Input roll number
Input marks of 5 subjects
Calculate average
вҶ’ avg = (m1 + m2 + m3 + m4 + m5) / 5
Display student details
Assign grade based on average:
avg вүҘ 90 вҶ’ Grade A
avg вүҘ 80 вҶ’ Grade B
avg вүҘ 70 вҶ’ Grade C
avg вүҘ 60 вҶ’ Grade D
else вҶ’ Grade F
Display grade
Write data to file using fprintf()
Close the file
Display success message
Stop
Flowchart
