рҹ”№ 7. Output Example

Enter student name: Ravi
Enter roll number: 101
Enter marks of 5 subjects: 85 90 88 92 87

Student Name: Ravi
Roll Number: 101
Average: 88.40
Grade: B

Record saved successfully in student_records.txt!
рҹ”№ 8. Advantages
Simple and easy to understand
Demonstrates file handling in C
Stores data permanently
Useful for basic student record systems
рҹ”№ 9. Limitations
Only handles one student at a time
No option to view or edit previous records
Limited validation of input
рҹ”№ 10. Conclusion
This project successfully demonstrates how to use file handling in C to store student records. It also shows the use of conditional statements and basic input/output operations.